========================================================================

Caller's Arguments:

Although this message left my TDoC several hours before the
end of last week, it was not distributed to list subscribers until
this week due to technical issues.  I believe that, according to
precedent, it should have taken effect this week; however, at the time
I sent the message, I was not aware that the list was down, and could
not be reasonably expected to be aware of this.  As the message has
now backfired on me (-2 ergs for me this week) despite the fact that
there was nothing unreasonable about my sending it originally, I argue
that my right to participate in the fora is violated unless its effect
is cancelled.

========================================================================

Caller's Evidence:

On Sun, Nov 14, 2010 at 12:28 PM, omd <c.ome.xk@gmail.com> wrote:
> I pay a fee to destroy one of scshunt's Rests.

========================================================================

