Gratuitous Arguments by omd:

1) I did send other messages after this one that also attempted to
destroy scshunt's rests.  At the time I sent the second message (in
which I forwarded the original to the backup forum), I was aware that
this might cause multiple rest destructions, but this was more of a
"best of two bad alternatives" scenario, and does not affect the fact
that I was unaware at the time of the original message.  The third
message was sent this week as a different action, and is basically
irrelevant.

2) I sent the original quoted message at the time shown in its Date:
header.  After that, Gmail probably attempted to resend it until it
went through, but that is out of my control.

========================================================================

Judge Yally's Arguments:

General precedent is that messages take effect when they are received,
as it would be illogical to pursue it in any other way. Too, your
right to participation in the fora was not violated because you were
still able to send messages to it. There existed many alternative
means for you to send that message immediately, including reserve fora
and individually messaging every player. Therefore, I judge TRUE.

========================================================================